🤖 **Common Clean Architecture mistakes and fixes.**

| Mistake | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Android in domain | Use pure Kotlin |
| ViewModel uses DAO | Use use cases |
| Wrong dependency | Follow dependency rule |
| Too many responsibilities | One per use case |
| No error handling | Handle errors |

**Fixes:**
```kotlin
// 1. Keep domain pure
class UseCase {
    suspend fun execute(): List<Player> {
        return repository.getPlayers()
    }
}

// 2. ViewModel uses use case
class ViewModel(
    private val getPlayers: GetPlayersUseCase
) : ViewModel() {
    fun loadPlayers() {
        viewModelScope.launch {
            val players = getPlayers()
        }
    }
}

// 3. Follow dependency rule
// Domain → Data (not the other way)

// 4. One responsibility per use case
class FilterPlayersUseCase
class SortPlayersUseCase

// 5. Handle errors
try {
    repository.getPlayers()
} catch (e: Exception) {
    // Handle error
}
```

